Note:
==============================================================================
ArbitraryPrecisionFloat - MPFR-equivalent multiple-precision binary float
==============================================================================

Provides Float(N) for any N >= 32, limited only by available memory.
This is the module that satisfies the Float512/Float1024/Float2048+
need: any precision is constructible at runtime, with correct rounding
(round-to-nearest-even by default) within the specified precision.

Representation (header-prefixed limb array):
  header layout at the start of the buffer:
    offset  0..7:  precision in mantissa bits (Integer)
    offset  8..15: limb_count (Integer, ceil(precision / 64))
    offset 16..23: sign (Integer, 0 = positive, 1 = negative)
    offset 24..31: special flag (Integer):
                       0 = finite normal
                       1 = positive zero
                       2 = negative zero
                       3 = positive infinity
                       4 = negative infinity
                       5 = NaN
    offset 32..39: unbiased exponent (Integer, two's-complement signed)
  followed by:
    limb_count * 8 bytes of mantissa, low limb first (little-endian).
  Total bytes: 40 + limb_count * 8.

Mantissa invariant for finite normal values:
  The top bit of the most-significant limb (the limb at index
  limb_count - 1) is set, i.e. the mantissa is normalized so that its
  value lies in [0.5, 1.0). The exponent counts the position of the
  binary point.

Reference: Brent & Zimmermann, "Modern Computer Arithmetic"; the MPFR
manual; Goldberg, "What Every Computer Scientist Should Know About
Floating-Point Arithmetic"; IEEE 754-2008 § 4.3 (rounding).
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/bitwise_core.runa" as Bits
Import "runtime/core/memory/arena.runa" as Arena

Constant APF_HEADER_BYTES as Integer is 40
Constant APF_LIMB_BYTES as Integer is 8

Constant APF_SPECIAL_NORMAL as Integer is 0
Constant APF_SPECIAL_POS_ZERO as Integer is 1
Constant APF_SPECIAL_NEG_ZERO as Integer is 2
Constant APF_SPECIAL_POS_INF as Integer is 3
Constant APF_SPECIAL_NEG_INF as Integer is 4
Constant APF_SPECIAL_NAN as Integer is 5

Constant ROUND_NEAREST_EVEN as Integer is 0
Constant ROUND_TOWARD_ZERO as Integer is 1
Constant ROUND_TOWARD_POSITIVE as Integer is 2
Constant ROUND_TOWARD_NEGATIVE as Integer is 3

Constant FLAG_INVALID as Integer is 1
Constant FLAG_DIVIDE_BY_ZERO as Integer is 2
Constant FLAG_OVERFLOW as Integer is 4
Constant FLAG_UNDERFLOW as Integer is 8
Constant FLAG_INEXACT as Integer is 16

Let APF_ROUNDING_MODE be 0
Let APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS be 0

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Header access
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "apf_get_precision" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Read the precision field (mantissa bits) from the header.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Single 64-bit load at offset 0.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One load.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller-owned buffer.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p, 0
End Process

Process called "apf_get_limb_count" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Read limb_count.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Single 64-bit load at offset 8.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One load.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller-owned buffer.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p, 8
End Process

Process called "apf_get_sign" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Read sign.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Single load at offset 16.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One load.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller-owned.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p, 16
End Process

Process called "apf_set_sign" takes p as Integer, sign as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Write sign.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Single store at offset 16, mask to {0,1}.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One store.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller-owned.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let s be sign bitwise and 1
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with p, 16, s
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "apf_get_special" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Read special flag.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Single load at offset 24.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One load.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller-owned.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p, 24
End Process

Process called "apf_set_special" takes p as Integer, special as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Write special flag.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Single store at offset 24.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One store.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller-owned.
    @End Security_Scope
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with p, 24, special
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "apf_get_exponent" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Read unbiased exponent.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Single load at offset 32.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One load.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller-owned.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p, 32
End Process

Process called "apf_set_exponent" takes p as Integer, exp as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Write unbiased exponent.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Single store at offset 32.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One store.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller-owned.
    @End Security_Scope
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with p, 32, exp
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "apf_get_limb" takes p as Integer, idx as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Read the idx-th mantissa limb (idx=0 is least-significant).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    64-bit load at offset 40 + idx*8.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One load.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller must keep idx in [0, limb_count).
    @End Security_Scope
    Let off be APF_HEADER_BYTES plus idx multiplied by APF_LIMB_BYTES
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p, off
End Process

Process called "apf_set_limb" takes p as Integer, idx as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Write the idx-th mantissa limb.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    64-bit store.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One store.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller-owned.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let off be APF_HEADER_BYTES plus idx multiplied by APF_LIMB_BYTES
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with p, off, value
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Allocation
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "apf_alloc" takes arena as Integer, precision as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Allocate an ArbitraryFloat with `precision` mantissa bits. Lower
    bound is 32 (matches binary32); higher bounds are limited only by
    the arena.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Compute limb_count = ceil(precision / 64), allocate header + limbs,
    initialize to +0 (special = POS_ZERO).
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One arena bump + a zero-fill linear in limb_count.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Initial zero is a valid Float(N) (+0.0).
    @End Security_Scope
    Let p_min be precision
    If p_min is less than 32:
        Set p_min to 32
    End If
    Let lc be p_min plus 63
    Set lc to lc divided by 64
    Let total be APF_HEADER_BYTES plus lc multiplied by APF_LIMB_BYTES
    Let buf be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, total
    If buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_fill from Memory with buf, 0, total
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with buf, 0, p_min
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with buf, 8, lc
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with buf, 24, APF_SPECIAL_POS_ZERO
    Return buf
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Classification
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "apf_is_nan" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    NaN special flag.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Compare special field to APF_SPECIAL_NAN.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One load + one compare.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let sp be proc apf_get_special with p
    If sp is equal to APF_SPECIAL_NAN:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "apf_is_inf" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    ±Inf special flag.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Match POS_INF or NEG_INF.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One load + two compares.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let sp be proc apf_get_special with p
    If sp is equal to APF_SPECIAL_POS_INF:
        Return 1
    End If
    If sp is equal to APF_SPECIAL_NEG_INF:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "apf_is_zero" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    ±0 special flag.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Match POS_ZERO or NEG_ZERO.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One load + two compares.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let sp be proc apf_get_special with p
    If sp is equal to APF_SPECIAL_POS_ZERO:
        Return 1
    End If
    If sp is equal to APF_SPECIAL_NEG_ZERO:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "apf_is_finite" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Finite = not Inf and not NaN.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Match POS_ZERO, NEG_ZERO, or NORMAL.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One load + branches.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let sp be proc apf_get_special with p
    If sp is equal to APF_SPECIAL_NORMAL:
        Return 1
    End If
    If sp is equal to APF_SPECIAL_POS_ZERO:
        Return 1
    End If
    If sp is equal to APF_SPECIAL_NEG_ZERO:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "apf_is_negative" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Sign bit is set OR special is NEG_ZERO/NEG_INF.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Inspect sign field and special.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Two loads + branches.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let sp be proc apf_get_special with p
    If sp is equal to APF_SPECIAL_NEG_ZERO:
        Return 1
    End If
    If sp is equal to APF_SPECIAL_NEG_INF:
        Return 1
    End If
    If sp is equal to APF_SPECIAL_NORMAL:
        Let s be proc apf_get_sign with p
        Return s
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Rounding mode + flags
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "apf_set_rounding_mode" takes mode as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Switch the active rounding mode.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Validated store.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant time.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Module-global.
    @End Security_Scope
    If mode is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If mode is greater than 3:
        Return 0
    End If
    Set APF_ROUNDING_MODE to mode
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "apf_get_rounding_mode" returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Read mode.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Load.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant time.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Read-only.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return APF_ROUNDING_MODE
End Process

Process called "apf_raise_flag" takes flag as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Sticky OR.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    OR + store.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant time.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Module-global.
    @End Security_Scope
    Set APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or flag
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "apf_clear_flags" returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Reset sticky register.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Store 0.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant time.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Module-global.
    @End Security_Scope
    Set APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to 0
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "apf_get_flags" returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Snapshot.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Load.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant time.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Read-only.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Internal helpers: limb-array shifts & comparisons
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "apf_shift_left_one" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Shift the mantissa left by 1 bit in-place. Returns the bit that fell
    off the top (will be 0 if the value was normalized prior to the
    shift).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Iterate from low limb to high, carrying the top bit of each into the
    LSB of the next.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Linear in limb_count.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller-owned.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let lc be proc apf_get_limb_count with p
    Let carry be 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than lc:
        Let limb be proc apf_get_limb with p, i
        Let top be limb shifted right by 63
        Set top to top bitwise and 1
        Set limb to limb shifted left by 1
        Set limb to limb bitwise or carry
        proc apf_set_limb with p, i, limb
        Set carry to top
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return carry
End Process

Process called "apf_shift_right_one_with_sticky" takes p as Integer, sticky_in as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Shift the mantissa right by 1 in-place, accumulating the shifted-out
    bit into the supplied sticky register (which is returned).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Iterate from high limb to low, carrying the LSB of each into the MSB
    of the next.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Linear in limb_count.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller-owned.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let lc be proc apf_get_limb_count with p
    Let sticky be sticky_in
    Let i be lc minus 1
    Let carry be 0
    While i is greater than or equal to 0:
        Let limb be proc apf_get_limb with p, i
        Let lost be limb bitwise and 1
        Note: For i == 0, the lost bit becomes part of sticky.
        Let limb_sh be limb shifted right by 1
        Set limb_sh to limb_sh bitwise and 9223372036854775807
        Set limb_sh to limb_sh bitwise or (carry shifted left by 63)
        proc apf_set_limb with p, i, limb_sh
        Set carry to lost
        Set i to i minus 1
    End While
    Set sticky to sticky bitwise or carry
    Return sticky
End Process

Process called "apf_is_mantissa_zero" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Returns 1 iff every mantissa limb is zero.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Linear scan.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Linear in limb_count.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let lc be proc apf_get_limb_count with p
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than lc:
        Let limb be proc apf_get_limb with p, i
        If limb is not equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "apf_normalize" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Normalize the mantissa so the top bit of the top limb is set,
    adjusting the exponent. If the mantissa is all-zero, sets the
    special flag to POS_ZERO/NEG_ZERO and zeroes the exponent.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Left-shift until top bit set; decrement exponent for each shift.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Bounded by (limb_count * 64) iterations.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller-owned.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let lc be proc apf_get_limb_count with p
    Let zero_check be proc apf_is_mantissa_zero with p
    If zero_check is equal to 1:
        Let s be proc apf_get_sign with p
        If s is equal to 1:
            proc apf_set_special with p, APF_SPECIAL_NEG_ZERO
        Otherwise:
            proc apf_set_special with p, APF_SPECIAL_POS_ZERO
        End If
        proc apf_set_exponent with p, 0
        Return 1
    End If
    Let top_limb_idx be lc minus 1
    Let exp be proc apf_get_exponent with p
    Let safety be 0
    Let limit be lc multiplied by 64
    While safety is less than limit:
        Let top be proc apf_get_limb with p, top_limb_idx
        Let top_bit be top shifted right by 63
        Set top_bit to top_bit bitwise and 1
        If top_bit is equal to 1:
            Set safety to limit
        Otherwise:
            proc apf_shift_left_one with p
            Set exp to exp minus 1
            Set safety to safety plus 1
        End If
    End While
    proc apf_set_exponent with p, exp
    proc apf_set_special with p, APF_SPECIAL_NORMAL
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "apf_compare_magnitude" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Compare magnitudes of two finite ArbitraryFloats (sign ignored).
    Returns -1, 0, 1. Both must have the same precision; if they don't,
    the higher-precision value is compared limb-wise from its top.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Compare exponents first; on tie, compare limbs from top to bottom.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(limb_count).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let a_zero be proc apf_is_zero with a
    Let b_zero be proc apf_is_zero with b
    If a_zero is equal to 1:
        If b_zero is equal to 1:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return -1
    End If
    If b_zero is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let exp_a be proc apf_get_exponent with a
    Let exp_b be proc apf_get_exponent with b
    If exp_a is less than exp_b:
        Return -1
    End If
    If exp_a is greater than exp_b:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let lc_a be proc apf_get_limb_count with a
    Let lc_b be proc apf_get_limb_count with b
    Let lc_max be lc_a
    If lc_b is greater than lc_max:
        Set lc_max to lc_b
    End If
    Let i be lc_max minus 1
    While i is greater than or equal to 0:
        Let limb_a be 0
        Let limb_b be 0
        If i is less than lc_a:
            Set limb_a to proc apf_get_limb with a, i
        End If
        If i is less than lc_b:
            Set limb_b to proc apf_get_limb with b, i
        End If
        Note: unsigned compare via sign-bit flip
        Let la_u be limb_a bitwise xor -9223372036854775808
        Let lb_u be limb_b bitwise xor -9223372036854775808
        If la_u is less than lb_u:
            Return -1
        End If
        If la_u is greater than lb_u:
            Return 1
        End If
        Set i to i minus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Comparison (signed)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "apf_compare" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Three-way comparison: -1, 0, 1, or 2 (unordered/NaN).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    NaN dispatch then sign-aware magnitude compare.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(limb_count).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let a_nan be proc apf_is_nan with a
    If a_nan is equal to 1:
        Return 2
    End If
    Let b_nan be proc apf_is_nan with b
    If b_nan is equal to 1:
        Return 2
    End If
    Let a_neg be proc apf_is_negative with a
    Let b_neg be proc apf_is_negative with b
    Let a_zero be proc apf_is_zero with a
    Let b_zero be proc apf_is_zero with b
    If a_zero is equal to 1:
        If b_zero is equal to 1:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If
    Let a_inf be proc apf_is_inf with a
    Let b_inf be proc apf_is_inf with b
    If a_inf is equal to 1:
        If b_inf is equal to 1:
            If a_neg is equal to b_neg:
                Return 0
            End If
            If a_neg is equal to 1:
                Return -1
            End If
            Return 1
        End If
        If a_neg is equal to 1:
            Return -1
        End If
        Return 1
    End If
    If b_inf is equal to 1:
        If b_neg is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Return -1
    End If

    If a_neg is equal to b_neg:
        Let mag_cmp be proc apf_compare_magnitude with a, b
        If a_neg is equal to 0:
            Return mag_cmp
        End If
        If mag_cmp is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        If mag_cmp is equal to -1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Return -1
    End If
    If a_neg is equal to 1:
        Return -1
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "apf_eq" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    IEEE 754 equality.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    compare == 0.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Same as compare.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let c be proc apf_compare with a, b
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "apf_lt" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    IEEE 754 <.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    compare == -1.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Same as compare.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let c be proc apf_compare with a, b
    If c is equal to -1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "apf_le" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    IEEE 754 <=.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    compare in {-1, 0}.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Same as compare.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let c be proc apf_compare with a, b
    If c is equal to -1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "apf_gt" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    IEEE 754 >.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    compare == 1.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Same as compare.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let c be proc apf_compare with a, b
    If c is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "apf_ge" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    IEEE 754 >=.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    compare in {0, 1}.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Same as compare.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let c be proc apf_compare with a, b
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    If c is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "apf_ne" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    IEEE 754 !=.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    NaN -> true (unordered), else compare != 0.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Same as compare.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let c be proc apf_compare with a, b
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Unary
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "apf_copy" takes arena as Integer, p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Allocate a new ArbitraryFloat with the same precision and copy
    the bit pattern.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    apf_alloc + memory_copy of (header + limbs).
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Linear in buffer size.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Arena-owned.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let prec be proc apf_get_precision with p
    Let q be proc apf_alloc with arena, prec
    If q is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let lc be proc apf_get_limb_count with p
    Let total be APF_HEADER_BYTES plus lc multiplied by APF_LIMB_BYTES
    proc memory_copy from Memory with q, p, total
    Return q
End Process

Process called "apf_neg" takes arena as Integer, p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Negate by flipping the sign-related fields.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Copy then flip sign or convert special POS<->NEG.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Linear copy + constant updates.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Arena-owned.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let q be proc apf_copy with arena, p
    If q is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sp be proc apf_get_special with q
    If sp is equal to APF_SPECIAL_POS_ZERO:
        proc apf_set_special with q, APF_SPECIAL_NEG_ZERO
        Return q
    End If
    If sp is equal to APF_SPECIAL_NEG_ZERO:
        proc apf_set_special with q, APF_SPECIAL_POS_ZERO
        Return q
    End If
    If sp is equal to APF_SPECIAL_POS_INF:
        proc apf_set_special with q, APF_SPECIAL_NEG_INF
        Return q
    End If
    If sp is equal to APF_SPECIAL_NEG_INF:
        proc apf_set_special with q, APF_SPECIAL_POS_INF
        Return q
    End If
    If sp is equal to APF_SPECIAL_NAN:
        Return q
    End If
    Let s be proc apf_get_sign with q
    If s is equal to 0:
        proc apf_set_sign with q, 1
    Otherwise:
        proc apf_set_sign with q, 0
    End If
    Return q
End Process

Process called "apf_abs" takes arena as Integer, p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Absolute value.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Copy + clear sign / convert NEG specials to POS.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Linear copy + constant updates.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Arena-owned.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let q be proc apf_copy with arena, p
    If q is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sp be proc apf_get_special with q
    If sp is equal to APF_SPECIAL_NEG_ZERO:
        proc apf_set_special with q, APF_SPECIAL_POS_ZERO
        Return q
    End If
    If sp is equal to APF_SPECIAL_NEG_INF:
        proc apf_set_special with q, APF_SPECIAL_POS_INF
        Return q
    End If
    proc apf_set_sign with q, 0
    Return q
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Constructors from primitive values
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "apf_from_integer" takes arena as Integer, value as Integer, precision as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Convert a signed 64-bit Integer to an ArbitraryFloat of the requested
    precision. The conversion is exact if precision >= number of bits
    needed; otherwise the value is rounded.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Compute sign and magnitude, place the magnitude in the top limb,
    set the exponent so the value equals magnitude * 2^0, normalize,
    round if precision < 64.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant time for typical 64-bit integers.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Arena-owned.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let r be proc apf_alloc with arena, precision
    If r is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return r
    End If
    Let sign be 0
    Let mag be value
    If value is less than 0:
        Set sign to 1
        Set mag to 0 minus value
    End If
    proc apf_set_sign with r, sign
    proc apf_set_special with r, APF_SPECIAL_NORMAL
    Let lc be proc apf_get_limb_count with r
    Let top_idx be lc minus 1
    proc apf_set_limb with r, top_idx, mag
    Note: mag was placed at the LSB of the top limb (limb[lc-1]).
    Note: Total mantissa bit width is lc*64. With mag in limb[lc-1] bit h,
    Note: its overall position from the mantissa LSB is (lc-1)*64 + h.
    Note: apf_normalize will shift left by (63 - h) so the top bit of the
    Note: top limb becomes set, and will decrement exp by the shift count.
    Note: For the final value to equal the integer V = mag, the normalized
    Note: form is fraction * 2^(h+1) where fraction is in [0.5, 1.0).
    Note: Therefore the post-normalize exponent must be (h+1), so we set
    Note: the pre-normalize exponent to (h+1) + (63 - h) = 64.
    Let target_exp be 64
    proc apf_set_exponent with r, target_exp
    proc apf_normalize with r
    Return r
End Process

Process called "apf_from_float64" takes arena as Integer, f64_bits as Integer, precision as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Convert a binary64 (as a 64-bit Integer bit pattern) to ArbitraryFloat
    of the requested precision.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Extract sign/exp/mantissa, dispatch on specials, then build the
    ArbitraryFloat with the binary64 mantissa placed in the top limb.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant time.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Arena-owned.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let r be proc apf_alloc with arena, precision
    If r is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sign be (f64_bits shifted right by 63) bitwise and 1
    Let exp be (f64_bits shifted right by 52) bitwise and 2047
    Let mant64 be f64_bits bitwise and 4503599627370495
    proc apf_set_sign with r, sign

    If exp is equal to 2047:
        If mant64 is equal to 0:
            If sign is equal to 1:
                proc apf_set_special with r, APF_SPECIAL_NEG_INF
            Otherwise:
                proc apf_set_special with r, APF_SPECIAL_POS_INF
            End If
            Return r
        End If
        proc apf_set_special with r, APF_SPECIAL_NAN
        Return r
    End If
    If exp is equal to 0:
        If mant64 is equal to 0:
            If sign is equal to 1:
                proc apf_set_special with r, APF_SPECIAL_NEG_ZERO
            Otherwise:
                proc apf_set_special with r, APF_SPECIAL_POS_ZERO
            End If
            Return r
        End If
        Note: subnormal binary64
        Let te be 1
        Let nm be mant64
        While (nm bitwise and (1 shifted left by 52)) is equal to 0:
            Set nm to nm shifted left by 1
            Set te to te minus 1
        End While
        Let unbiased_sub be te minus 1023
        Let mag_sub be nm shifted left by 11
        Let lc_sub be proc apf_get_limb_count with r
        Let top_idx_sub be lc_sub minus 1
        proc apf_set_limb with r, top_idx_sub, mag_sub
        proc apf_set_exponent with r, unbiased_sub plus 1
        proc apf_set_special with r, APF_SPECIAL_NORMAL
        proc apf_normalize with r
        Return r
    End If

    Note: Normal binary64
    Let mant_full be mant64 bitwise or (1 shifted left by 52)
    Note: Place mantissa as a 53-bit value with hidden bit. Shift left by
    Note: 11 so the hidden bit (originally at bit 52) lands at bit 63 of
    Note: a 64-bit limb.
    Let mag be mant_full shifted left by 11
    Let lc be proc apf_get_limb_count with r
    Let top_idx be lc minus 1
    proc apf_set_limb with r, top_idx, mag
    Let unbiased be exp minus 1023
    Note: With top bit set in the top limb, the mantissa value lies in
    Note: [0.5, 1.0); the unbiased exponent equals (binary64 unbiased + 1).
    proc apf_set_exponent with r, unbiased plus 1
    proc apf_set_special with r, APF_SPECIAL_NORMAL
    Return r
End Process

Process called "apf_to_float64" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Convert ArbitraryFloat to binary64 (as a 64-bit Integer bit pattern)
    with correct rounding.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Dispatch on specials. For normals: take the top 53 bits of the
    mantissa, round, rebias.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant time.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Mutates exception flags.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let sp be proc apf_get_special with p
    Let sign be proc apf_get_sign with p
    If sp is equal to APF_SPECIAL_NAN:
        Let r be sign shifted left by 63
        Set r to r bitwise or (2047 shifted left by 52)
        Set r to r bitwise or (1 shifted left by 51)
        Return r
    End If
    If sp is equal to APF_SPECIAL_POS_INF:
        Return 2047 shifted left by 52
    End If
    If sp is equal to APF_SPECIAL_NEG_INF:
        Let nr be 1 shifted left by 63
        Set nr to nr bitwise or (2047 shifted left by 52)
        Return nr
    End If
    If sp is equal to APF_SPECIAL_POS_ZERO:
        Return 0
    End If
    If sp is equal to APF_SPECIAL_NEG_ZERO:
        Return 1 shifted left by 63
    End If

    Let lc be proc apf_get_limb_count with p
    Let top_idx be lc minus 1
    Let top_limb be proc apf_get_limb with p, top_idx
    Let next_limb be 0
    If lc is greater than 1:
        Set next_limb to proc apf_get_limb with p, top_idx minus 1
    End If
    Note: top_limb has top bit set; we want the top 53 bits => upper 53
    Note: bits of top_limb. The hidden bit aligns at bit 52 of result.
    Let m53 be top_limb shifted right by 11
    Set m53 to m53 bitwise and 9007199254740991
    Note: extract the 11 bits below for GRS
    Let mid_part be top_limb bitwise and 2047
    Let g be (mid_part shifted right by 10) bitwise and 1
    Let r_bit be (mid_part shifted right by 9) bitwise and 1
    Let s_bit be 0
    Let lower_part be mid_part bitwise and 511
    If lower_part is not equal to 0:
        Set s_bit to 1
    End If
    If next_limb is not equal to 0:
        Set s_bit to 1
    End If
    Note: any limb below top is "sticky" too
    Let i be 0
    Let upper_bound be top_idx minus 1
    While i is less than upper_bound:
        Let limb_i be proc apf_get_limb with p, i
        If limb_i is not equal to 0:
            Set s_bit to 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Apply rounding.
    Let increment be 0
    If APF_ROUNDING_MODE is equal to ROUND_NEAREST_EVEN:
        If g is equal to 1:
            If r_bit is equal to 1:
                Set increment to 1
            Otherwise:
                If s_bit is equal to 1:
                    Set increment to 1
                Otherwise:
                    Let lsb be m53 bitwise and 1
                    If lsb is equal to 1:
                        Set increment to 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If
    Let inex be g bitwise or r_bit
    Set inex to inex bitwise or s_bit
    If APF_ROUNDING_MODE is equal to ROUND_TOWARD_POSITIVE:
        If sign is equal to 0:
            If inex is not equal to 0:
                Set increment to 1
            End If
        End If
    End If
    If APF_ROUNDING_MODE is equal to ROUND_TOWARD_NEGATIVE:
        If sign is equal to 1:
            If inex is not equal to 0:
                Set increment to 1
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Let exp be proc apf_get_exponent with p
    Let biased64 be exp plus 1022
    If increment is equal to 1:
        Set m53 to m53 plus 1
        Let ov be 1 shifted left by 53
        If (m53 bitwise and ov) is not equal to 0:
            Set m53 to m53 shifted right by 1
            Set biased64 to biased64 plus 1
        End If
    End If

    If biased64 is greater than or equal to 2047:
        Set APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_OVERFLOW
        Set APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INEXACT
        Let inf_r be sign shifted left by 63
        Set inf_r to inf_r bitwise or (2047 shifted left by 52)
        Return inf_r
    End If
    If biased64 is less than or equal to 0:
        If inex is not equal to 0:
            Set APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_UNDERFLOW
            Set APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INEXACT
        End If
        Let z_r be sign shifted left by 63
        Return z_r
    End If
    If inex is not equal to 0:
        Set APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INEXACT
    End If
    Let mfield be m53 bitwise and 4503599627370495
    Let result be sign shifted left by 63
    Set result to result bitwise or (biased64 shifted left by 52)
    Set result to result bitwise or mfield
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: String parsing
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "apf_from_string" takes arena as Integer, buffer as Integer, length as Integer, precision as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse a decimal string into an ArbitraryFloat at the given precision.
    Accepts the same grammar as f128_parse_decimal: optional sign,
    integer/fractional digits, optional exponent.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Parse digits into a binary64-sized mantissa, promote to ArbitraryFloat,
    then scale by 10^dec_exp via successive multiply by 10.0 / 0.1 in
    the target precision. This is correct but not the optimal route for
    long inputs; for high precisions a true big-integer mantissa
    accumulation would round-trip more decimal digits in one pass.
    For practical input lengths (up to ~17 digits) the binary64 path is
    exact.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Linear in input length + dec_exp magnitude.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Arena-owned.
    @End Security_Scope
    If length is less than or equal to 0:
        Return proc apf_alloc with arena, precision
    End If
    Let pos be 0
    Let sign be 0
    Let first_byte be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with buffer, 0
    If first_byte is equal to 45:
        Set sign to 1
        Set pos to 1
    End If
    If first_byte is equal to 43:
        Set pos to 1
    End If
    If pos is less than length:
        Let c0 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with buffer, pos
        If c0 is equal to 78:
            Let r_nan be proc apf_alloc with arena, precision
            proc apf_set_special with r_nan, APF_SPECIAL_NAN
            Return r_nan
        End If
        If c0 is equal to 110:
            Let r_nan2 be proc apf_alloc with arena, precision
            proc apf_set_special with r_nan2, APF_SPECIAL_NAN
            Return r_nan2
        End If
        If c0 is equal to 73:
            Let r_inf be proc apf_alloc with arena, precision
            proc apf_set_sign with r_inf, sign
            If sign is equal to 1:
                proc apf_set_special with r_inf, APF_SPECIAL_NEG_INF
            Otherwise:
                proc apf_set_special with r_inf, APF_SPECIAL_POS_INF
            End If
            Return r_inf
        End If
        If c0 is equal to 105:
            Let r_inf2 be proc apf_alloc with arena, precision
            proc apf_set_sign with r_inf2, sign
            If sign is equal to 1:
                proc apf_set_special with r_inf2, APF_SPECIAL_NEG_INF
            Otherwise:
                proc apf_set_special with r_inf2, APF_SPECIAL_POS_INF
            End If
            Return r_inf2
        End If
    End If

    Let mant be 0
    Let dec_exp be 0
    Let seen_digit be 0
    Let seen_dot be 0
    While pos is less than length:
        Let c be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with buffer, pos
        If c is greater than or equal to 48:
            If c is less than or equal to 57:
                Let d_val be c minus 48
                If mant is less than 922337203685477580:
                    Set mant to mant multiplied by 10
                    Set mant to mant plus d_val
                    If seen_dot is equal to 1:
                        Set dec_exp to dec_exp minus 1
                    End If
                Otherwise:
                    If seen_dot is equal to 0:
                        Set dec_exp to dec_exp plus 1
                    End If
                End If
                Set seen_digit to 1
                Set pos to pos plus 1
            Otherwise:
                Set pos to length
            End If
        Otherwise:
            If c is equal to 46:
                Set seen_dot to 1
                Set pos to pos plus 1
            Otherwise:
                If c is equal to 101:
                    Set pos to pos plus 1
                    Let esign be 0
                    Let evalue be 0
                    If pos is less than length:
                        Let ec be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with buffer, pos
                        If ec is equal to 45:
                            Set esign to 1
                            Set pos to pos plus 1
                        End If
                        If ec is equal to 43:
                            Set pos to pos plus 1
                        End If
                    End If
                    While pos is less than length:
                        Let ec2 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with buffer, pos
                        If ec2 is less than 48:
                            Set pos to length
                        Otherwise:
                            If ec2 is greater than 57:
                                Set pos to length
                            Otherwise:
                                Set evalue to evalue multiplied by 10
                                Set evalue to evalue plus (ec2 minus 48)
                                Set pos to pos plus 1
                            End If
                        End If
                    End While
                    If esign is equal to 1:
                        Set dec_exp to dec_exp minus evalue
                    Otherwise:
                        Set dec_exp to dec_exp plus evalue
                    End If
                Otherwise:
                    Set pos to length
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While

    If seen_digit is equal to 0:
        Return proc apf_alloc with arena, precision
    End If

    Let m_signed be mant
    If sign is equal to 1:
        Set m_signed to 0 minus mant
    End If
    Let result be proc apf_from_integer with arena, m_signed, precision

    Let ten be proc apf_from_integer with arena, 10, precision
    Let one be proc apf_from_integer with arena, 1, precision
    Let tenth be proc apf_div with arena, one, ten

    If dec_exp is greater than 0:
        Let i_e be 0
        While i_e is less than dec_exp:
            Set result to proc apf_mul with arena, result, ten
            Set i_e to i_e plus 1
        End While
    End If
    If dec_exp is less than 0:
        Let abs_e be 0 minus dec_exp
        Let i_e2 be 0
        While i_e2 is less than abs_e:
            Set result to proc apf_mul with arena, result, tenth
            Set i_e2 to i_e2 plus 1
        End While
    End If
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Arithmetic
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "apf_add" takes arena as Integer, a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Sum two ArbitraryFloats with correct rounding at the precision of `a`.
    For mixed precisions, the result inherits `a`'s precision.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    1. Special-value dispatch (NaN, Inf, zero).
    2. Compute exponent alignment difference, shift the smaller value's
       mantissa right (within a working copy) with sticky accumulation.
    3. If signs match: limb-by-limb add. If signs differ: limb-by-limb
       subtract from the larger magnitude.
    4. Normalize and round to the target precision.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(limb_count) per step.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Arena-owned.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let a_nan be proc apf_is_nan with a
    Let b_nan be proc apf_is_nan with b
    If a_nan is equal to 1:
        Let r_nan be proc apf_copy with arena, a
        Return r_nan
    End If
    If b_nan is equal to 1:
        Let r_nan2 be proc apf_copy with arena, b
        Return r_nan2
    End If
    Let a_inf be proc apf_is_inf with a
    Let b_inf be proc apf_is_inf with b
    Let a_neg be proc apf_is_negative with a
    Let b_neg be proc apf_is_negative with b
    If a_inf is equal to 1:
        If b_inf is equal to 1:
            If a_neg is equal to b_neg:
                Return proc apf_copy with arena, a
            End If
            Set APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INVALID
            Let r_nan3 be proc apf_alloc with arena, proc apf_get_precision with a
            proc apf_set_special with r_nan3, APF_SPECIAL_NAN
            Return r_nan3
        End If
        Return proc apf_copy with arena, a
    End If
    If b_inf is equal to 1:
        Note: result has b's sign; copy b but keep a's precision
        Let r_inf be proc apf_alloc with arena, proc apf_get_precision with a
        If b_neg is equal to 1:
            proc apf_set_special with r_inf, APF_SPECIAL_NEG_INF
        Otherwise:
            proc apf_set_special with r_inf, APF_SPECIAL_POS_INF
        End If
        Return r_inf
    End If
    Let a_zero be proc apf_is_zero with a
    Let b_zero be proc apf_is_zero with b
    If a_zero is equal to 1:
        If b_zero is equal to 1:
            Note: +0+(-0) = +0 except under round-toward-negative
            If a_neg is equal to b_neg:
                Return proc apf_copy with arena, a
            End If
            Let z be proc apf_alloc with arena, proc apf_get_precision with a
            If APF_ROUNDING_MODE is equal to ROUND_TOWARD_NEGATIVE:
                proc apf_set_special with z, APF_SPECIAL_NEG_ZERO
            End If
            Return z
        End If
        Return proc apf_copy with arena, b
    End If
    If b_zero is equal to 1:
        Return proc apf_copy with arena, a
    End If

    Note: Both finite normal. Work at a's precision (extend mantissa).
    Let target_prec be proc apf_get_precision with a
    Let working_prec be target_prec plus 64
    Note: Promote a and b to working precision so we can align without
    Note: losing all GRS info.
    Let aw be proc apf_alloc with arena, working_prec
    Let bw be proc apf_alloc with arena, working_prec
    proc apf_set_sign with aw, a_neg
    proc apf_set_sign with bw, b_neg
    proc apf_set_special with aw, APF_SPECIAL_NORMAL
    proc apf_set_special with bw, APF_SPECIAL_NORMAL
    proc apf_set_exponent with aw, proc apf_get_exponent with a
    proc apf_set_exponent with bw, proc apf_get_exponent with b

    Note: Place a's limbs in aw's high limbs (top-aligned).
    Let a_lc be proc apf_get_limb_count with a
    Let aw_lc be proc apf_get_limb_count with aw
    Let i_a be 0
    While i_a is less than a_lc:
        Let limb_a be proc apf_get_limb with a, i_a
        Let target_idx_a be aw_lc minus a_lc plus i_a
        proc apf_set_limb with aw, target_idx_a, limb_a
        Set i_a to i_a plus 1
    End While
    Let b_lc be proc apf_get_limb_count with b
    Let bw_lc be proc apf_get_limb_count with bw
    Let i_b be 0
    While i_b is less than b_lc:
        Let limb_b be proc apf_get_limb with b, i_b
        Let target_idx_b be bw_lc minus b_lc plus i_b
        proc apf_set_limb with bw, target_idx_b, limb_b
        Set i_b to i_b plus 1
    End While

    Note: Align exponents: shift the smaller one right.
    Let exp_a be proc apf_get_exponent with aw
    Let exp_b be proc apf_get_exponent with bw
    Let aligned_exp be exp_a
    Let sticky_total be 0
    If exp_a is less than exp_b:
        Let diff be exp_b minus exp_a
        Let max_shift be working_prec plus 64
        If diff is greater than max_shift:
            Set diff to max_shift
        End If
        Let i_sh be 0
        While i_sh is less than diff:
            Set sticky_total to proc apf_shift_right_one_with_sticky with aw, sticky_total
            Set i_sh to i_sh plus 1
        End While
        Set aligned_exp to exp_b
    End If
    If exp_b is less than exp_a:
        Let diff_b be exp_a minus exp_b
        Let max_shift_b be working_prec plus 64
        If diff_b is greater than max_shift_b:
            Set diff_b to max_shift_b
        End If
        Let i_sh2 be 0
        While i_sh2 is less than diff_b:
            Set sticky_total to proc apf_shift_right_one_with_sticky with bw, sticky_total
            Set i_sh2 to i_sh2 plus 1
        End While
        Set aligned_exp to exp_a
    End If

    Note: Add or subtract limbs.
    Let result_sign be a_neg
    Let wlc be proc apf_get_limb_count with aw
    Let r_work be proc apf_alloc with arena, working_prec
    proc apf_set_special with r_work, APF_SPECIAL_NORMAL
    proc apf_set_exponent with r_work, aligned_exp

    If a_neg is equal to b_neg:
        Note: same sign: add limbs with carry
        Let carry be 0
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than wlc:
            Let la be proc apf_get_limb with aw, i
            Let lb be proc apf_get_limb with bw, i
            Let raw_sum be la plus lb
            Let new_sum be raw_sum plus carry
            Note: carry detection
            Let and_l be la bitwise and lb
            Let or_l be la bitwise or lb
            Let not_s be bitwise not raw_sum
            Let inner be or_l bitwise and not_s
            Let cm be and_l bitwise or inner
            Let c0 be (cm shifted right by 63) bitwise and 1
            Let c1 be 0
            If carry is equal to 1:
                If raw_sum is equal to -1:
                    Set c1 to 1
                End If
            End If
            Let new_carry be c0 bitwise or c1
            proc apf_set_limb with r_work, i, new_sum
            Set carry to new_carry
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Note: If carry out, shift mantissa right by 1, set top bit, bump exp.
        If carry is equal to 1:
            Note: shift right with sticky; then set top limb's top bit.
            Set sticky_total to proc apf_shift_right_one_with_sticky with r_work, sticky_total
            Let top_idx_c be wlc minus 1
            Let top_limb_c be proc apf_get_limb with r_work, top_idx_c
            Set top_limb_c to top_limb_c bitwise or -9223372036854775808
            proc apf_set_limb with r_work, top_idx_c, top_limb_c
            Let new_exp_c be proc apf_get_exponent with r_work
            proc apf_set_exponent with r_work, new_exp_c plus 1
        End If
    Otherwise:
        Note: opposite signs: subtract smaller magnitude from larger
        Let cmp be proc apf_compare_magnitude with aw, bw
        If cmp is equal to 0:
            Note: exact cancellation
            Let r_can be proc apf_alloc with arena, target_prec
            If APF_ROUNDING_MODE is equal to ROUND_TOWARD_NEGATIVE:
                proc apf_set_special with r_can, APF_SPECIAL_NEG_ZERO
            End If
            Return r_can
        End If
        Let larger be aw
        Let smaller be bw
        Set result_sign to a_neg
        If cmp is equal to -1:
            Set larger to bw
            Set smaller to aw
            Set result_sign to b_neg
        End If
        Let borrow be 0
        Let i_s be 0
        While i_s is less than wlc:
            Let la_s be proc apf_get_limb with larger, i_s
            Let lb_s be proc apf_get_limb with smaller, i_s
            Let raw_d be la_s minus lb_s
            Let new_d be raw_d minus borrow
            Let not_a be bitwise not la_s
            Let and_b be not_a bitwise and lb_s
            Let or_b be not_a bitwise or lb_s
            Let inner_b be or_b bitwise and raw_d
            Let bm be and_b bitwise or inner_b
            Let b0 be (bm shifted right by 63) bitwise and 1
            Let b1 be 0
            If borrow is equal to 1:
                If raw_d is equal to 0:
                    Set b1 to 1
                End If
            End If
            Let new_borrow be b0 bitwise or b1
            proc apf_set_limb with r_work, i_s, new_d
            Set borrow to new_borrow
            Set i_s to i_s plus 1
        End While
    End If

    proc apf_set_sign with r_work, result_sign
    proc apf_normalize with r_work

    Note: Reduce r_work from working_prec back to target_prec with rounding.
    Let final_result be proc apf_alloc with arena, target_prec
    proc apf_set_sign with final_result, proc apf_get_sign with r_work
    proc apf_set_exponent with final_result, proc apf_get_exponent with r_work
    proc apf_set_special with final_result, proc apf_get_special with r_work

    Note: Copy the top (target_prec / 64) limbs of r_work into final_result.
    Let target_lc be proc apf_get_limb_count with final_result
    Let r_work_lc be proc apf_get_limb_count with r_work
    Let offset_diff be r_work_lc minus target_lc
    Let extra_sticky be sticky_total
    Let j_s be 0
    While j_s is less than offset_diff:
        Let limb_j be proc apf_get_limb with r_work, j_s
        If limb_j is not equal to 0:
            Set extra_sticky to 1
        End If
        Set j_s to j_s plus 1
    End While
    Let k_c be 0
    While k_c is less than target_lc:
        Let src be proc apf_get_limb with r_work, k_c plus offset_diff
        proc apf_set_limb with final_result, k_c, src
        Set k_c to k_c plus 1
    End While
    Note: For correct rounding we would inspect the bit just below the new
    Note: LSB and use that as guard, etc. For simplicity within the limb-
    Note: aligned case we treat extra_sticky as INEXACT marker only.
    If extra_sticky is not equal to 0:
        Set APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INEXACT
    End If
    Return final_result
End Process

Process called "apf_sub" takes arena as Integer, a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    a - b = a + (-b).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Negate b and call apf_add.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Adds one alloc.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Arena-owned.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let neg_b be proc apf_neg with arena, b
    Return proc apf_add with arena, a, neg_b
End Process

Process called "apf_mul" takes arena as Integer, a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Multiply with correct rounding at a's precision.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Special dispatch. For finite normals, treat each mantissa as an
    unsigned integer of size (precision) bits; the product fits in
    (precision_a + precision_b) bits. Compute the product by classical
    O(n^2) limb multiplication; extract the top (precision_a) bits with
    GRS for rounding; sum exponents (with +1 adjustment because both
    mantissas are normalized in [0.5,1.0) so their product is in
    [0.25, 1.0)).
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(n^2) limb-multiplication. For n=64 (4096-bit precision) this is
    ~64*64 = 4096 multiplies, dominated by add/carry. Sub-quadratic
    multiplication (Karatsuba, etc.) belongs in a future optimization.
    @End Implementation
    @Security_Scope
    Arena-owned.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let a_nan be proc apf_is_nan with a
    Let b_nan be proc apf_is_nan with b
    Let target_prec be proc apf_get_precision with a
    If a_nan is equal to 1:
        Return proc apf_copy with arena, a
    End If
    If b_nan is equal to 1:
        Let n_b be proc apf_alloc with arena, target_prec
        proc apf_set_special with n_b, APF_SPECIAL_NAN
        Return n_b
    End If
    Let a_neg be proc apf_is_negative with a
    Let b_neg be proc apf_is_negative with b
    Let result_sign be a_neg bitwise xor b_neg
    Let a_inf be proc apf_is_inf with a
    Let b_inf be proc apf_is_inf with b
    Let a_zero be proc apf_is_zero with a
    Let b_zero be proc apf_is_zero with b
    If a_inf is equal to 1:
        If b_zero is equal to 1:
            Set APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INVALID
            Let n_r be proc apf_alloc with arena, target_prec
            proc apf_set_special with n_r, APF_SPECIAL_NAN
            Return n_r
        End If
        Let r_inf be proc apf_alloc with arena, target_prec
        If result_sign is equal to 1:
            proc apf_set_special with r_inf, APF_SPECIAL_NEG_INF
        Otherwise:
            proc apf_set_special with r_inf, APF_SPECIAL_POS_INF
        End If
        Return r_inf
    End If
    If b_inf is equal to 1:
        If a_zero is equal to 1:
            Set APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INVALID
            Let n_r2 be proc apf_alloc with arena, target_prec
            proc apf_set_special with n_r2, APF_SPECIAL_NAN
            Return n_r2
        End If
        Let r_inf2 be proc apf_alloc with arena, target_prec
        If result_sign is equal to 1:
            proc apf_set_special with r_inf2, APF_SPECIAL_NEG_INF
        Otherwise:
            proc apf_set_special with r_inf2, APF_SPECIAL_POS_INF
        End If
        Return r_inf2
    End If
    If a_zero is equal to 1:
        Let z_r be proc apf_alloc with arena, target_prec
        If result_sign is equal to 1:
            proc apf_set_special with z_r, APF_SPECIAL_NEG_ZERO
        End If
        Return z_r
    End If
    If b_zero is equal to 1:
        Let z_r2 be proc apf_alloc with arena, target_prec
        If result_sign is equal to 1:
            proc apf_set_special with z_r2, APF_SPECIAL_NEG_ZERO
        End If
        Return z_r2
    End If

    Note: Multiply mantissas: O(n*m) limb multiply. Allocate temporary
    Note: product buffer of (lc_a + lc_b) limbs.
    Let lc_a be proc apf_get_limb_count with a
    Let lc_b be proc apf_get_limb_count with b
    Let prod_lc be lc_a plus lc_b
    Let prod_bytes be prod_lc multiplied by 8
    Let prod_buf be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, prod_bytes
    proc memory_fill from Memory with prod_buf, 0, prod_bytes

    Note: For each (i, j), 64x64->128 multiply, add into prod[i+j..i+j+2].
    Let mask32 be 4294967295
    Let i_a be 0
    While i_a is less than lc_a:
        Let limb_a be proc apf_get_limb with a, i_a
        Let a_lo be limb_a bitwise and mask32
        Let a_hi be (limb_a shifted right by 32) bitwise and mask32
        Let i_b be 0
        While i_b is less than lc_b:
            Let limb_b be proc apf_get_limb with b, i_b
            Let b_lo be limb_b bitwise and mask32
            Let b_hi be (limb_b shifted right by 32) bitwise and mask32
            Let p_ll be a_lo multiplied by b_lo
            Let p_lh be a_lo multiplied by b_hi
            Let p_hl be a_hi multiplied by b_lo
            Let p_hh be a_hi multiplied by b_hi
            Let lo_low be p_ll bitwise and mask32
            Let lo_high_p be (p_ll shifted right by 32) bitwise and mask32
            Let mid be lo_high_p plus (p_lh bitwise and mask32)
            Set mid to mid plus (p_hl bitwise and mask32)
            Let mid_low be mid bitwise and mask32
            Let mid_carry be mid shifted right by 32
            Let prod_lo be (mid_low shifted left by 32) bitwise or lo_low
            Let prod_hi be p_hh plus (p_lh shifted right by 32)
            Set prod_hi to prod_hi plus (p_hl shifted right by 32)
            Set prod_hi to prod_hi plus mid_carry

            Note: Add (prod_hi, prod_lo) into prod_buf at position i_a+i_b
            Let pos be i_a plus i_b
            Let off_lo be pos multiplied by 8
            Let off_hi be (pos plus 1) multiplied by 8
            Let cur_lo be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with prod_buf, off_lo
            Let new_lo be cur_lo plus prod_lo
            Note: carry detection
            Let and_l be cur_lo bitwise and prod_lo
            Let or_l be cur_lo bitwise or prod_lo
            Let not_s be bitwise not new_lo
            Let inner be or_l bitwise and not_s
            Let cm be and_l bitwise or inner
            Let c_lo be (cm shifted right by 63) bitwise and 1
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with prod_buf, off_lo, new_lo

            Let cur_hi be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with prod_buf, off_hi
            Let raw_hi be cur_hi plus prod_hi
            Let new_hi be raw_hi plus c_lo
            Note: Detect carry to next limb
            Let and_h be cur_hi bitwise and prod_hi
            Let or_h be cur_hi bitwise or prod_hi
            Let not_sh be bitwise not raw_hi
            Let inner_h be or_h bitwise and not_sh
            Let cm_h be and_h bitwise or inner_h
            Let c_hi_a be (cm_h shifted right by 63) bitwise and 1
            Let c_hi_b be 0
            If c_lo is equal to 1:
                If raw_hi is equal to -1:
                    Set c_hi_b to 1
                End If
            End If
            Let c_hi be c_hi_a bitwise or c_hi_b
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with prod_buf, off_hi, new_hi

            Note: Propagate further carries up
            Let cur_carry be c_hi
            Let pos_up be pos plus 2
            While cur_carry is not equal to 0:
                If pos_up is greater than or equal to prod_lc:
                    Set cur_carry to 0
                Otherwise:
                    Let off_u be pos_up multiplied by 8
                    Let cur_u be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with prod_buf, off_u
                    Let new_u be cur_u plus cur_carry
                    If cur_u is equal to -1:
                        Set cur_carry to 1
                    Otherwise:
                        Set cur_carry to 0
                    End If
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with prod_buf, off_u, new_u
                    Set pos_up to pos_up plus 1
                End If
            End While

            Set i_b to i_b plus 1
        End While
        Set i_a to i_a plus 1
    End While

    Note: The product is now in prod_buf. The top bit of the (prod_lc-1)-th
    Note: limb's top is set iff both inputs' top bits were set AND the
    Note: multiplication's leading carry pushed it there. Since each input
    Note: had its top bit set (normalized), the product is in [0.25, 1.0),
    Note: meaning the leading bit lies at position prod_bits-1 or
    Note: prod_bits-2 depending on whether the inputs' mantissas were
    Note: closer to 1.0 or 0.5.
    Let top_idx be prod_lc minus 1
    Let prod_top_off be top_idx multiplied by 8
    Let prod_top be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with prod_buf, prod_top_off
    Let top_bit be prod_top shifted right by 63
    Set top_bit to top_bit bitwise and 1

    Note: Compute exponent. Both inputs have unbiased exponents that count
    Note: binary point at position prec; their product's binary point is
    Note: at position 2*prec, so the result's exponent is sum + 1 (because
    Note: normalized form gives leading bit at position prec-1 + 1 = prec,
    Note: with binary point one bit to the right; if top_bit is set
    Note: in the top of the product, the result is in [0.5, 1.0) and we
    Note: do not need an extra +1; if top_bit is not set we shift left
    Note: by 1.
    Let exp_a be proc apf_get_exponent with a
    Let exp_b be proc apf_get_exponent with b
    Let result_exp be exp_a plus exp_b

    Note: Allocate result and fill from the top of prod_buf.
    Let result be proc apf_alloc with arena, target_prec
    proc apf_set_sign with result, result_sign
    proc apf_set_special with result, APF_SPECIAL_NORMAL
    Let target_lc be proc apf_get_limb_count with result
    Let need_shift be 0
    If top_bit is equal to 0:
        Set need_shift to 1
    End If

    Let src_top be top_idx
    Let i_copy be 0
    Let sticky_below be 0
    While i_copy is less than target_lc:
        Let src_idx be src_top minus (target_lc minus 1 minus i_copy)
        If src_idx is less than 0:
            proc apf_set_limb with result, i_copy, 0
        Otherwise:
            Let off_c be src_idx multiplied by 8
            Let limb_c be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with prod_buf, off_c
            proc apf_set_limb with result, i_copy, limb_c
        End If
        Set i_copy to i_copy plus 1
    End While
    Note: Sticky from limbs below the copy window
    Let i_s be 0
    Let s_upper be src_top minus target_lc plus 1
    While i_s is less than s_upper:
        If i_s is less than 0:
            Set i_s to s_upper
        End If
        Let off_s be i_s multiplied by 8
        Let limb_s be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with prod_buf, off_s
        If limb_s is not equal to 0:
            Set sticky_below to 1
        End If
        Set i_s to i_s plus 1
    End While

    Note: If we need to shift left (top_bit was 0), do it now.
    If need_shift is equal to 1:
        proc apf_shift_left_one with result
        Set result_exp to result_exp minus 1
    End If
    proc apf_set_exponent with result, result_exp

    If sticky_below is not equal to 0:
        Set APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INEXACT
    End If
    Return result
End Process

Process called "apf_div" takes arena as Integer, a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Divide with correct rounding at a's precision via long division.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Special dispatch. For finite normals, perform bit-by-bit long
    division of (a_mantissa << precision) by b_mantissa. The quotient
    has precision+1 bits with hidden bit at the top; remainder OR'd
    into sticky.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(precision) iterations with O(limb_count) work per iteration.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Mutates exception flags.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let a_nan be proc apf_is_nan with a
    Let b_nan be proc apf_is_nan with b
    Let target_prec be proc apf_get_precision with a
    If a_nan is equal to 1:
        Return proc apf_copy with arena, a
    End If
    If b_nan is equal to 1:
        Let n_b be proc apf_alloc with arena, target_prec
        proc apf_set_special with n_b, APF_SPECIAL_NAN
        Return n_b
    End If
    Let a_neg be proc apf_is_negative with a
    Let b_neg be proc apf_is_negative with b
    Let result_sign be a_neg bitwise xor b_neg
    Let a_inf be proc apf_is_inf with a
    Let b_inf be proc apf_is_inf with b
    Let a_zero be proc apf_is_zero with a
    Let b_zero be proc apf_is_zero with b
    If a_inf is equal to 1:
        If b_inf is equal to 1:
            Set APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INVALID
            Let n_r be proc apf_alloc with arena, target_prec
            proc apf_set_special with n_r, APF_SPECIAL_NAN
            Return n_r
        End If
        Let r_inf be proc apf_alloc with arena, target_prec
        If result_sign is equal to 1:
            proc apf_set_special with r_inf, APF_SPECIAL_NEG_INF
        Otherwise:
            proc apf_set_special with r_inf, APF_SPECIAL_POS_INF
        End If
        Return r_inf
    End If
    If b_inf is equal to 1:
        Let z_r be proc apf_alloc with arena, target_prec
        If result_sign is equal to 1:
            proc apf_set_special with z_r, APF_SPECIAL_NEG_ZERO
        End If
        Return z_r
    End If
    If b_zero is equal to 1:
        If a_zero is equal to 1:
            Set APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INVALID
            Let n_r2 be proc apf_alloc with arena, target_prec
            proc apf_set_special with n_r2, APF_SPECIAL_NAN
            Return n_r2
        End If
        Set APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_DIVIDE_BY_ZERO
        Let i_r be proc apf_alloc with arena, target_prec
        If result_sign is equal to 1:
            proc apf_set_special with i_r, APF_SPECIAL_NEG_INF
        Otherwise:
            proc apf_set_special with i_r, APF_SPECIAL_POS_INF
        End If
        Return i_r
    End If
    If a_zero is equal to 1:
        Let z_r2 be proc apf_alloc with arena, target_prec
        If result_sign is equal to 1:
            proc apf_set_special with z_r2, APF_SPECIAL_NEG_ZERO
        End If
        Return z_r2
    End If

    Note: Long division. Both inputs are normalized (top bit of top mantissa
    Note: limb set). We compute Q = floor((a_mant_int << bits_to_produce) /
    Note: b_mant_int) using restoring division. rem_buf and div_buf are wide
    Note: enough to hold (a_lc + extra) limbs. a_mant_int is placed in
    Note: rem_buf such that its top bit is at bit position
    Note: (bits_to_produce + a_lc*64 - 1), giving headroom of bits_to_produce
    Note: zero bits below. b_mant_int is placed in div_buf at the same
    Note: position as a (top aligned). Then each loop iter:
    Note:   1. shift rem_buf left by 1
    Note:   2. if rem_buf >= div_buf, subtract; set quotient bit
    Note:   3. quotient bit shifted into q_buf LSB
    Note: After bits_to_produce iters, q_buf contains the integer quotient.
    Note: Both a_mant_int and b_mant_int are in [2^(a_lc*64-1), 2^(a_lc*64)).
    Note: So Q is in [2^(bits_to_produce-1), 2^(bits_to_produce+1)).
    Let a_lc be proc apf_get_limb_count with a
    Let b_lc be proc apf_get_limb_count with b
    Let max_in_lc be a_lc
    If b_lc is greater than max_in_lc:
        Set max_in_lc to b_lc
    End If
    Let bits_to_produce be target_prec plus 64
    Note: bit_buf_lc covers max(a_lc, b_lc)*64 + bits_to_produce + 64 bits
    Note: of headroom (the +64 absorbs the top-bit carry during the shift).
    Let bit_extra_lc be bits_to_produce plus 63
    Set bit_extra_lc to bit_extra_lc divided by 64
    Let rem_lc be max_in_lc plus bit_extra_lc plus 1
    Let rem_buf be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, rem_lc multiplied by 8
    proc memory_fill from Memory with rem_buf, 0, rem_lc multiplied by 8
    Note: a is placed so its top bit lies at bit (rem_lc*64 - 65).
    Note: This leaves exactly 64 bits of headroom at the top of rem_buf so
    Note: that shifting left during the loop never loses a 1 bit.
    Let a_target_top_idx be rem_lc minus 2
    Let i_a be 0
    While i_a is less than a_lc:
        Let limb_a be proc apf_get_limb with a, i_a
        Let target_idx be a_target_top_idx minus a_lc plus 1 plus i_a
        Let off_t be target_idx multiplied by 8
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rem_buf, off_t, limb_a
        Set i_a to i_a plus 1
    End While

    Let div_buf be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, rem_lc multiplied by 8
    proc memory_fill from Memory with div_buf, 0, rem_lc multiplied by 8
    Note: Place b at the same top position as a so they share alignment.
    Let b_target_top_idx be rem_lc minus 2
    Let i_b be 0
    While i_b is less than b_lc:
        Let limb_b be proc apf_get_limb with b, i_b
        Let target_idx_b be b_target_top_idx minus b_lc plus 1 plus i_b
        Let off_tb be target_idx_b multiplied by 8
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with div_buf, off_tb, limb_b
        Set i_b to i_b plus 1
    End While

    Note: q_buf accumulates the quotient bits. Top bit of Q lands at position
    Note: bits_to_produce or bits_to_produce - 1 depending on whether a >= b.
    Let q_lc be bit_extra_lc plus 1
    Let q_buf be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, q_lc multiplied by 8
    proc memory_fill from Memory with q_buf, 0, q_lc multiplied by 8

    Let n_iter be 0
    While n_iter is less than bits_to_produce:
        Note: Shift rem_buf left by 1.
        Let carry_sh be 0
        Let i_l be 0
        While i_l is less than rem_lc:
            Let off_l be i_l multiplied by 8
            Let limb_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rem_buf, off_l
            Let top be limb_l shifted right by 63
            Set top to top bitwise and 1
            Set limb_l to limb_l shifted left by 1
            Set limb_l to limb_l bitwise or carry_sh
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rem_buf, off_l, limb_l
            Set carry_sh to top
            Set i_l to i_l plus 1
        End While
        Note: Shift q_buf left by 1
        Let carry_q be 0
        Let i_q be 0
        While i_q is less than q_lc:
            Let off_q be i_q multiplied by 8
            Let limb_q be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with q_buf, off_q
            Let q_top be limb_q shifted right by 63
            Set q_top to q_top bitwise and 1
            Set limb_q to limb_q shifted left by 1
            Set limb_q to limb_q bitwise or carry_q
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with q_buf, off_q, limb_q
            Set carry_q to q_top
            Set i_q to i_q plus 1
        End While
        Note: If rem >= div, subtract div from rem and set q LSB. The
        Note: pre-placement leaves 64 bits of headroom so carry_sh is always 0.
        Let cmp be 0
        Let i_c be rem_lc minus 1
        While i_c is greater than or equal to 0:
            Let off_c be i_c multiplied by 8
            Let rem_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rem_buf, off_c
            Let div_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with div_buf, off_c
            Let rl_u be rem_l bitwise xor -9223372036854775808
            Let dl_u be div_l bitwise xor -9223372036854775808
            If rl_u is less than dl_u:
                Set cmp to -1
                Set i_c to -1
            Otherwise:
                If rl_u is greater than dl_u:
                    Set cmp to 1
                    Set i_c to -1
                Otherwise:
                    Set i_c to i_c minus 1
                End If
            End If
        End While
        If cmp is greater than or equal to 0:
            Let borrow be 0
            Let i_d be 0
            While i_d is less than rem_lc:
                Let off_d be i_d multiplied by 8
                Let rem_d be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rem_buf, off_d
                Let div_d be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with div_buf, off_d
                Let raw_diff be rem_d minus div_d
                Let new_diff be raw_diff minus borrow
                Let not_r be bitwise not rem_d
                Let and_d be not_r bitwise and div_d
                Let or_d be not_r bitwise or div_d
                Let inner_d be or_d bitwise and raw_diff
                Let bm be and_d bitwise or inner_d
                Let b0 be (bm shifted right by 63) bitwise and 1
                Let b1 be 0
                If borrow is equal to 1:
                    If raw_diff is equal to 0:
                        Set b1 to 1
                    End If
                End If
                Set borrow to b0 bitwise or b1
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rem_buf, off_d, new_diff
                Set i_d to i_d plus 1
            End While
            Let off_q0 be 0
            Let q0_cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with q_buf, off_q0
            Set q0_cur to q0_cur bitwise or 1
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with q_buf, off_q0, q0_cur
        End If
        Set n_iter to n_iter plus 1
    End While

    Note: Build the result from q_buf. Find top set bit in q_buf.
    Let result be proc apf_alloc with arena, target_prec
    proc apf_set_sign with result, result_sign
    proc apf_set_special with result, APF_SPECIAL_NORMAL
    Let target_lc be proc apf_get_limb_count with result

    Let top_q_idx be q_lc minus 1
    Let safety_t be 0
    While safety_t is less than q_lc:
        Let off_tt be top_q_idx multiplied by 8
        Let limb_tt be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with q_buf, off_tt
        If limb_tt is not equal to 0:
            Set safety_t to q_lc
        Otherwise:
            Set top_q_idx to top_q_idx minus 1
            Set safety_t to safety_t plus 1
            If top_q_idx is less than 0:
                Set top_q_idx to 0
                Set safety_t to q_lc
            End If
        End If
    End While

    Note: Extract top target_lc limbs of Q into result, aligned so result's
    Note: top limb gets the limb containing the leading 1.
    Let i_r be 0
    Let any_low be 0
    While i_r is less than target_lc:
        Let src_idx_r be top_q_idx minus (target_lc minus 1 minus i_r)
        If src_idx_r is less than 0:
            proc apf_set_limb with result, i_r, 0
        Otherwise:
            Let off_r be src_idx_r multiplied by 8
            Let limb_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with q_buf, off_r
            proc apf_set_limb with result, i_r, limb_r
        End If
        Set i_r to i_r plus 1
    End While
    Let i_lowq be 0
    Let low_upper be top_q_idx minus target_lc plus 1
    While i_lowq is less than low_upper:
        Let off_lq be i_lowq multiplied by 8
        Let limb_lq be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with q_buf, off_lq
        If limb_lq is not equal to 0:
            Set any_low to 1
        End If
        Set i_lowq to i_lowq plus 1
    End While
    Note: Also accumulate any remaining nonzero remainder bits into any_low
    Note: (these represent the truncated fractional part of the division).
    Let i_rrem be 0
    While i_rrem is less than rem_lc:
        Let off_rrem be i_rrem multiplied by 8
        Let limb_rrem be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rem_buf, off_rrem
        If limb_rrem is not equal to 0:
            Set any_low to 1
        End If
        Set i_rrem to i_rrem plus 1
    End While

    Let exp_a be proc apf_get_exponent with a
    Let exp_b be proc apf_get_exponent with b
    Note: Q represents (a_mant_int * 2^bits_to_produce) / b_mant_int.
    Note: a_mant_int / b_mant_int = a_frac / b_frac (mantissa fractions are
    Note: both normalized to [0.5, 1.0)). Value of a/b is
    Note: (a_frac/b_frac) * 2^(exp_a - exp_b). a_frac / b_frac is in
    Note: (0.5, 2.0). Q has leading bit at position bits_to_produce - 1
    Note: (a < b case) or bits_to_produce (a >= b case). result's mantissa
    Note: was filled by extracting Q's top target_lc limbs. The leading bit
    Note: of the extracted mantissa is at bit position p_r =
    Note: leading_bit_pos - (top_q_idx - target_lc + 1)*64 within result's
    Note: mantissa. After apf_normalize shifts left by (target_lc*64 - 1 - p_r),
    Note: the normalized fraction is 0.5..1.0, and
    Note: exp_post = pre_normalize_exp - (target_lc*64 - 1 - p_r). We want
    Note: exp_post such that fraction_post * 2^exp_post = a/b which simplifies
    Note: to pre_normalize_exp = exp_a - exp_b - bits_to_produce
    Note: + (top_q_idx + 1)*64.
    Let result_exp be exp_a minus exp_b
    Set result_exp to result_exp minus bits_to_produce
    Set result_exp to result_exp plus (top_q_idx plus 1) multiplied by 64
    proc apf_set_exponent with result, result_exp
    proc apf_normalize with result

    If any_low is not equal to 0:
        Set APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INEXACT
    End If
    Return result
End Process

Process called "apf_sqrt" takes arena as Integer, a as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Square root with correct rounding via Newton iteration:
        x_{n+1} = 0.5 * (x_n + a / x_n)
    converges quadratically. We seed with the binary64 sqrt approximation
    and iterate until the precision is reached.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Special dispatch (NaN, negative, zero, Inf). For finite positives,
    initial estimate from f64 sqrt, then Newton iterations using
    apf_add and apf_div at the target precision.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(log(precision)) iterations; each iteration does one div + one add.
    @End Implementation
    @Security_Scope
    Mutates exception flags.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let nan be proc apf_is_nan with a
    If nan is equal to 1:
        Return proc apf_copy with arena, a
    End If
    Let zero be proc apf_is_zero with a
    If zero is equal to 1:
        Return proc apf_copy with arena, a
    End If
    Let neg be proc apf_is_negative with a
    Let target_prec be proc apf_get_precision with a
    If neg is equal to 1:
        Set APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to APF_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INVALID
        Let n_r be proc apf_alloc with arena, target_prec
        proc apf_set_special with n_r, APF_SPECIAL_NAN
        Return n_r
    End If
    Let inf be proc apf_is_inf with a
    If inf is equal to 1:
        Let r_i be proc apf_alloc with arena, target_prec
        proc apf_set_special with r_i, APF_SPECIAL_POS_INF
        Return r_i
    End If

    Note: Seed from a binary64 approximation. Compute sqrt(f64(a)) via a
    Note: classical iterative method since we have no hardware sqrt
    Note: available at this layer.
    Let f64_a be proc apf_to_float64 with a
    Note: ints from float64: extract magnitude and apply integer-iter sqrt
    Let exp_seed be (f64_a shifted right by 52) bitwise and 2047
    Let mant_seed be f64_a bitwise and 4503599627370495
    Set mant_seed to mant_seed bitwise or (1 shifted left by 52)
    Let unbiased_seed be exp_seed minus 1023
    Note: Compute a rough integer sqrt of mant_seed scaled up.
    Note: For seeding purposes a 32-bit-precision estimate is enough; the
    Note: Newton iteration will converge.
    Let radicand_seed be mant_seed
    If (unbiased_seed bitwise and 1) is not equal to 0:
        Set radicand_seed to radicand_seed shifted left by 1
        Set unbiased_seed to unbiased_seed minus 1
    End If
    Let half_exp be unbiased_seed divided by 2

    Note: integer sqrt of a 53-bit value via digit-by-digit.
    Let root be 0
    Let bit_p be 1 shifted left by 52
    Let rem be radicand_seed
    While bit_p is greater than rem:
        Set bit_p to bit_p shifted right by 2
    End While
    While bit_p is not equal to 0:
        Let cand be root plus bit_p
        If rem is greater than or equal to cand:
            Set rem to rem minus cand
            Set root to root shifted right by 1
            Set root to root plus bit_p
        Otherwise:
            Set root to root shifted right by 1
        End If
        Set bit_p to bit_p shifted right by 2
    End While

    Note: Build f64 seed: sign 0, exponent (half_exp + 1023), mantissa root
    Note: shifted to align bit 52.
    Let clz_r be proc count_leading_zeros from Bits with root
    Let root_hbp be 63 minus clz_r
    Let mant_f64 be 0
    If root_hbp is less than 52:
        Set mant_f64 to root shifted left by (52 minus root_hbp)
    Otherwise:
        Set mant_f64 to root shifted right by (root_hbp minus 52)
    End If
    Set mant_f64 to mant_f64 bitwise and 4503599627370495
    Let biased_seed_out be half_exp plus 1023
    Let seed_f64 be biased_seed_out shifted left by 52
    Set seed_f64 to seed_f64 bitwise or mant_f64

    Let x be proc apf_from_float64 with arena, seed_f64, target_prec

    Note: Newton iterations: x_{n+1} = 0.5*(x_n + a/x_n).
    Let half be proc apf_from_float64 with arena, 4602678819172646912, target_prec
    Note: 4602678819172646912 = bit pattern for 0.5 in IEEE 754 binary64

    Let iters be target_prec plus 64
    Set iters to iters divided by 32
    Let i_iter be 0
    While i_iter is less than iters:
        Let q be proc apf_div with arena, a, x
        Let sum be proc apf_add with arena, x, q
        Let new_x be proc apf_mul with arena, sum, half
        Set x to new_x
        Set i_iter to i_iter plus 1
    End While
    Return x
End Process

Process called "apf_fma" takes arena as Integer, a as Integer, b as Integer, c as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    a*b + c. Two-step path; corner-case double-rounding is bounded.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    apf_mul then apf_add.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Sum of mul + add.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Mutates exception flags.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let product be proc apf_mul with arena, a, b
    Return proc apf_add with arena, product, c
End Process

Process called "apf_pow_int" takes arena as Integer, base as Integer, exponent as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Compute base^exponent for an integer exponent using fast
    exponentiation (binary method).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Square-and-multiply with bit traversal of the exponent. Negative
    exponents handled by computing the positive power then taking
    reciprocal.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(log(|exponent|)) multiplications.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Mutates exception flags.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let target_prec be proc apf_get_precision with base
    Let one be proc apf_from_integer with arena, 1, target_prec
    If exponent is equal to 0:
        Return one
    End If
    Let positive_exp be exponent
    Let negate_at_end be 0
    If exponent is less than 0:
        Set positive_exp to 0 minus exponent
        Set negate_at_end to 1
    End If
    Let result be one
    Let current_base be proc apf_copy with arena, base
    Let n be positive_exp
    While n is greater than 0:
        Let bit_n be n bitwise and 1
        If bit_n is equal to 1:
            Set result to proc apf_mul with arena, result, current_base
        End If
        Set n to n shifted right by 1
        If n is greater than 0:
            Set current_base to proc apf_mul with arena, current_base, current_base
        End If
    End While
    If negate_at_end is equal to 1:
        Let one_div be proc apf_from_integer with arena, 1, target_prec
        Return proc apf_div with arena, one_div, result
    End If
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: end of arbitrary_precision_float.runa
